        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 4:14PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 414 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Todd Creek, or 18 miles north of Denver, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Thornton, northeastern Commerce City, eastern Northglenn,
Brighton, northeastern Denver International Airport, Frederick,
Fort Lupton, Lochbuie, Dacono, Hudson, Barr Lake, Todd Creek,
Wattenburg and Henderson.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

If on a lake, get out of the water and secure loose items. Boaters
can expect strong gusty winds and locally higher waves. Boaters
should seek safe harbor immediately.</instruction>
